8. Why this matters

Because most real thinking is not done as equations.

It’s done as:
	•	“this fits”
	•	“that breaks”
	•	“this leads there”
	•	“that survives the condition”
	•	“this is closer to stable”

CFM-1 gives that layer a notation.

So it’s useful for:
	•	AI reasoning traces
	•	planning
	•	proof search
	•	system design
	•	narrative logic
	•	prompt interpretation

